cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about biomedical image segmentation using deep convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for this task, which involves multi-scale dense connections and quantization, indicating potential contributions to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on a specific dataset, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
